items.title: Israel is committing genocide in Gaza, Amnesty International says
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Amnesty International accused Israel of committing genocide in the Gaza Strip during its war with Hamas, saying it has sought to deliberately destroy Palestinians by mounting deadly attacks, demolishing vital infrastructure, and preventing the delivery of food, medicine and other aid. items.title: Hamas official says Gaza ceasefire talks have resumed after weekslong hiatus
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
A Hamas official said Thursday that international mediators have resumed negotiating with the militant group and Israel over a ceasefire in Gaza, and that he was hopeful a deal to end the 14-month war was within reach. Ceasefire negotiations were halted last month when Qatar suspended talks with mediators from Egypt and the United States because of frustration over a lack of progress between Israel and Hamas. But there has been a resumption of efforts in recent days to end the fighting, release hostages from Gaza and free Palestinian prisoners in Israel, according to Bassem Naim, an official in Hamas’ political bureau who spoke with The Associated Press in Turkey. (AP video: Mehmet Guzel, Ayse Wieting). Read more: https://bit.ly/49nc3jc

items.title: LIVE: View of the Beirut skyline in Lebanon
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Lebanon’s Health Ministry and state media say Israeli forces have carried out several drone and artillery strikes in southern Lebanon, killing one person. The new strikes further shake a tenuous 6-day-old ceasefire, a day after Israeli launched its heaviest barrage of the south of the past week in retaliation to what Hezbollah called a “warning” volley responding to earlier Israeli strikes. Read more here: https://bit.ly/4eZNbiE

#beirut #lebanon #israel #news #live

items.title: Severely ill children and their families in Gaza face fraught wait on evacuation requests
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:

items.title: Young Ghanaians bemoan unemployment and inflation ahead of Saturday’s election
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Ghana is often upheld as an exemplary democracy in West Africa, where many countries have experienced coups in recent years. The country has far outpaced many of its neighbours in development. But ahead of Saturday’s elections, voters, especially young people, are mostly worried about the economy.

items.title: LIVE: South Korea’s ruling party holds an emergency meeting in parliament
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from inside South Korea's parliament as the People Power Party holds a closed-door emergency meeting.
South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol is facing possible impeachment for sending heavily armed soldiers into Seoul's streets with a declaration of martial law that reminded many of the country’s past military-backed dictatorships.
